    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-06-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-06-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1891</hi>.</date> (Received June
                        26.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan informs the Department that the Chilean Government can not be expected
                    to grant the favors referred to in the telegram of the 17th, since the telegraph
                    company has refused to open direct communications with Valparaiso.</p>
            </div>
